sections.paragraphs:
Albert was married in 1124 to [[Sophie of Winzenburg]] (died 25 March 1160) and they had the following children:
# [[Otto I, Margrave of Brandenburg]] (1126/1128&ndash;7 March 1184){{sfn|Lyon|2013|p=241}}
# Count [[Hermann I of Orlamünde]] (died 1176){{sfn|Lyon|2013|p=241}}
# [[Siegfried, Count of Anhalt|Siegfried]] (died 24 October 1184), [[Bishopric of Brandenburg|Bishop of Brandenburg]] from 1173–1180, [[Archbishop of Bremen|Prince-Archbishop of Bremen]], the first ranked prince, from 1180–1184{{sfn|Lyon|2013|p=241}}
# Heinrich (died 1185), a canon in [[Magdeburg]]
# Count [[Albert of Ballenstedt]] (died after 6 December 1172)
# Count [[Dietrich of Werben]] (died after 5 September 1183){{sfn|Lyon|2013|p=241}}
# Count [[Bernhard, Count of Anhalt|Bernhard of Anhalt]] (1134&ndash;9 February 1212), [[Duke of Saxony]] from 1180-1212 as Bernard III
# [[Hedwig of Brandenburg|Hedwig]] (d. 1203), married to [[Otto II, Margrave of Meissen]]{{sfn|Lyon|2013|p=241}}
# Daughter, married c. 1152 to [[Vladislav of Bohemia]]
# Adelheid (died 1162), a nun in [[Lamspringe]]
# Gertrude, married in 1155 to Duke [[Děpold I of Jamnitz|Diepold of Moravia]]
# Sybille (died c. 1170), Abbess of [[Quedlinburg Abbey|Quedlinburg]]
# Eilika

